        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Well, to answer my own question, I finally got off my lazy arse and went to CS for some hunting.  The drakes don't pose a very big problem at all, as the aggro range even while KoS is very small (fought a wyvern that was about 20 feet or less from another wyvern without aggro).  Haven't tried root dotting the wyverns yet, and probably won't.</P><P>Anyway, I gotta say the exp and loot here seems WAY better than Seafuries.  I made 3 blues and looted 4 quest gems (and 2 peridots) in about 2 hours or less (wasn't paying too much attention) and the pulling was only hampered by my neurotic need to be as close to full mana as possible before the next pull lol (i med till i'm down by two bubbles of health, then pull).</P><P>Here is how I do it:<BR>At 51, only 5 spells are needed for root dotting... Dooming Darkness to pull, then Paralyzing Earth (most times one cast lasts through an entire fight), then Splurt and Ignite Blood, then Bond of Death for healing.   If ParaEarth resists the first time, then I cast BoD before IB, as I time the darkness by BoD.  When BoD wears off, Darkness will go right after, so reapply if necessary.  Those 4 DoTs will kill the wyvern no problem.</P><P><img src="http://www.the-den.org/eq/z-small.jpg" border=0><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45366" target="_New">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45366</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
