        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=78709&TOPIC_ID=8755&FORUM_ID=53&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=Hunting+49&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I did 51-52 in CS and after experimenting with a lot of spells here is what I think is the best combination for me. First forget about the pet.</P><P>Cascading darkness, Splurt, BoD = dead wyvern<BR>Cascading darkness, Splurt, BoD = dead cobalt drake.</P><P>Yes, they have the same number of HPs and those 3 spells will kill them. I use Root because for some reason PE breaks too soon for me. Using Root I got almost no resists and it takes only 2 Roots = 60 mana. If PE breaks, there goes 100 mana. How do I kill them:</P><P>1. If I can kill them in the same place as they spawn, I just root, cascading, splurt, bod. reaply root and it's done.</P><P>2. If I need to pull it away (maybe I know something spawns there, or this fucking shellfish collector comes by) I cast Splurt, run a bit to a safe spot, root, Cascading, BoD. Reaply root when breaks and you got one dead wyvern. </P><P>With cobalt drakes you use the same dots, but I always pull with Cascading and always cast on them from maximum casting distance. If it sticks, then root, splur, bod and med at max casting distance. Their AoE hurts. If Cascading its resisted and you dont have Jboots/SoW you are more less dead, they fly faster than you run. If you have Jboots you will outrun the drake. Just put some distance distance, root, Cascading again, splurt, BoD and med at max casting distance. </P><P>The reason I use Cascading and not Dooming is because I need a snare and I need the 1k of damage that Cascading does. I have tried with Dooming and EB instead of cascading, but it is not as mana efficient. With this spell lineup I finish fight with the same ammount of mana as I had when I started (if no resists). And they die right as splurt and cascading wear off, pretty nice. You can chain pull, assuming the damn quad kiting wizards and druids leave you something to pull ..</P><P>Good luck :)</P><P>---<BR>Heretic of Cold Comfort Clan<BR>Ayonae Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

